    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Colors comprising hues that have been reduced in intensity by the addition of white, making pastel colors, such as cream and pink; or of black, producing the earth colors, such as mustard and moss green, or of both white and black, creating the neutralized hues, or color-tinged grays, such as oatmeal and charcoal.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046682/Random House Dictionary of the English Language (1987)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Kleuren bestaande uit kleurschakeringen die zijn gedempt door toevoeging van wit, waardoor pastelkleuren zoals crème en roze ontstaan; of door toevoeging van zwart, resulterend in aardtinten als mosterdgroen en mosgroen, of door toevoeging van zowel wit als zwart, waardoor neutrale kleurschakeringen of grijzen met een kleurzweem ontstaan, zoals beigegrijs en antracietgrijs.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052403/Van Dale Groot Woordenboek (1998)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099102/Van Dale Ne-En (1991)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>色調強度降低的顏色。降低色調強度的方式是加入白色，變成乳白、粉紅等柔和的淡色；或加入黑色，變成芥末綠或蘚苔綠等的大地色；或加入黑色與白色，變成中性的色調，或有些許色彩的灰色，像是燕麥色、煤炭色等。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Cores que compreendem matizes que foram reduzidos em intensidade pela adição de branco, produzindo cores pastéis, como creme e rosa; ou de preto, produzindo cores terrosas, como mostarda e verde musgo, ou de branco e preto, criando matizes neutralizados, ou cinzas tingidos de cores, como aveia e carvão.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109633/CVAA-BR Consortium (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
